<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Barrett asks if Secretary Root will accept invitation of Colombia to
                            stop a day at Cartagena en route Panama-New York. The minister of
                            foreign affairs will be sent to meet the Secretary on his arrival.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>